name: CoronaryArteryDiseaseI10
title: Coronary artery disease I10
description: I20.8, I24.8, and possibly I25.89 become non-billable 2024
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Definition:This value set intends to capture all ICD-10 CM diagnosis codes that represent atherosclerotic heart disease (CAD).),(Data Element Scope: CONDITION: CLINICAL_DRIVER:),(Inclusion Criteria: "CAD: Angina- I20*; Acute MI - I21*; Subsequent MI- I22*; Complications Following MI -I23*; Other Acute Ischemic Heart Dz- I24*; Chronic Ischemic Heart Dz- I25*, H/o MI, H/o CABG, H/o stent in place, old MI),(Exclusion Criteria: ICD-10 and SCT  codes that are not representative of atherosclerosis: Coronary artery spasm angina-87343002)
